# 🐳 Docker Networking & Container Commands Cheat Sheet

A complete guide to Docker basics, container management, and networking (bridge + custom networks).

--------------------------------------------------

📦 1. Install Docker (Ubuntu)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

(Log out & log back in after adding user to docker group)

--------------------------------------------------

🔍 2. Verify Installation

docker --version
docker ps
docker images

--------------------------------------------------

📥 3. Pull Image

docker pull tsravanam/simple-app:latest

--------------------------------------------------

🚀 4. Run Container (Default Bridge Network)

docker run -d -p 8080:8080 --name cont1 tsravanam/simple-app:latest

--------------------------------------------------

📋 5. List Containers

docker ps        # Running containers
docker ps -a     # All containers

--------------------------------------------------

🖥️ 6. Enter Container

docker exec -it cont1 bash
OR
docker exec -it cont1 sh

--------------------------------------------------

🌐 7. Install ping inside container (Ubuntu/Debian)

apt update
apt install -y iputils-ping

--------------------------------------------------

🔌 8. List Networks

docker network ls

--------------------------------------------------

🧱 9. Create Custom Network

docker network create airtelnetwork

--------------------------------------------------

🚀 10. Run Container in Custom Network

docker run -d -p 8082:8080 --name cont3 --network airtelnetwork tsravanam/simple-app:latest

--------------------------------------------------

🔍 11. Inspect Network

docker network inspect airtelnetwork

--------------------------------------------------

🔗 12. Connect Existing Container to Custom Network

docker network connect airtelnetwork cont1

--------------------------------------------------

❌ 13. Disconnect Container from Custom Network

docker network disconnect airtelnetwork cont1
